Sentencas: An electrolyte supported solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) using standard electrodes, doped-lanthanum manganite cathode and Ni-cermet anode, was operated with direct (anhydrous) ethanol for more than 100 h, delivering essentially the same power output as running on hydrogen.
Titulo: Direct ethanol solid oxide fuel cell operating in gradual internal reforming

Sentencas: A ceria-based layer provides the catalytic activity for the gradual internal reforming, which uses the steam formed by the electrochemical oxidation of hydrogen for the decomposition of ethanol.
Titulo: Direct ethanol solid oxide fuel cell operating in gradual internal reforming

Sentencas: Such a concept opens up the way for multi-fuel SOFCs using standard components and a catalytic layer.
Titulo: Direct ethanol solid oxide fuel cell operating in gradual internal reforming
